In view of the foregoing observations noted above, we recommend that the GAD Focal Point System:
Strictly comply with the provisions of Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2013-01 of the PCW-DILG-DBM-NEDA and other applicable rulings relative to the submission of the approved GAD Plan and Budget and the preparation of the Annual GAD Accomplishment Reports to be approved by the different offices concerned and expenditures should be limited to the amount approved in the GAD Plan and Budget to ensure that all planned projects and activities are implemented;
Require the Heads of the implementing offices to ensure that GAD programs, projects and activities are implemented as planned to attain the GAD objectives;
Maximize the utilization of the GAD funds through the implementation of GAD-related programs and projects on order to attain the objective for which the funds were provided;
Require the GAD Focal Point System to: a. institutionalize the GAD database with adequate and systematically gathered sex-disaggregated data which will provide the bases for gender analysis, planning, programming and policy formulation; b. undertake gender analysis to identify and confirm existing gender issues and ensure that the programs, projects and activities are responsive to the said issues; and c. revisit Annex B of PCW-DILG-DBM-NEDA Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2013-01 which identifies the data requirements for particular gender issues; and
Establish a GAD monitoring and evaluation system as required under Section 3.4 and 5.1 of PCW-DILG-DBM-NEDA Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2013-01.

